def check():
    n = int(input())
    a = list(map(int, input().split()))
    b = list(map(int, input().split()))
    c = list(map(int, input().split()))
    d = list(map(int, input().split()))
    for i in range(n):
        if a[i] == b[i] or a[i] == c[i] or a[i] == d[i] or b[i] == c[i] or b[i] == d[i] or c[i] == d[i]:
            print("NO")
            return
    print("YES")
    print(a[0], b[0])

#!/bin/python3

import sys

n = int(input().strip())
a = [int(a_temp) for a_temp in input().strip().split(' ')]

if n % 2 != 0:
    print("NO")
    sys.exit(0)

if len(set(a)) != len(a):
    print("NO")
    sys.exit(0)

print("YES")
print(min(a), max(a))
